{
  "texts": [
    "This distribution highlights the importance of combining content views (e.g., title and abstract) for improved understanding.",
    "V. Experiments",
    "We conduct our experiments using the MIND dataset (Wu et al. 2020), a real-world news recommendation dataset collected from user behavior logs on Microsoft News.",
    "It is available in two versions: MIND-large, which contains over 15 million impression logs generated by 1 million users, and MIND-small, a subset randomly sampled from 50,000 users, as detailed in Table 1.",
    "During training, we combine MIND-small and MIND-tiny to form the training set."
  ]
}